ing the history of science (computus, prognostication), the history of art, literature, theology (homilies, prayers, hagiography, contemplative texts), music, historiography and geography. Aspects of knowledge is aimed at an academic readership, including advanced undergraduate and postgraduate students, as well as specialists in medieval literature, history of science, history of knowledge, geography, theology, music, philosophy, intellectual history, history of language and material culture.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aBooks and reading. 0aKnowledge, Theory of. 0aLiterature, MedievalxHistory and criticism. 4aLiterature Studies 2020. 4aMedieval Studies 2020. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / General.2bisacsh  aGeography.  aHistory of Art.  aKnowledge.  aLearning.  aLiterature.  aMaterial Culture.  aMiddle Ages.  aMusic.  aScience.  aTheology.1 aBrown, Michelle P., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBuckley, Ann, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCesario, Marilina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCesario, Marilina, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aChardonnens, László Sándor, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aConklin Akbari, Suzanne, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMagennis, Hugh, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMagennis, Hugh, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aMittman, Asa Simon, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNorth, Richard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRenevey, Denis, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aScragg, Do